<foaf:title>Independent Researcher</foaf:title>

<rdfs:comment>
Nicholas Van-Orton is an independent researcher and project manager working on decentralized digital identity,
the semantic web, knowledge graphs, and digital humanities. His research explores the relationship between
autonomous computational systems and human interpretive capacity through the model of the Civilizational
Interpretive Ratio. He is also the founder and president of the Paris-based cultural and research association
NVO987 – Culture Visuelle Moderne et Contemporaine.
</rdfs:comment>

